---
import BaseLayout from '../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Work with me"
  description="Narrative strategy and editorial systems for organisations that have strong research and insight but aren't extracting full value from it."
>
  <article class="container-site py-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">

      <header class="mb-16">
        <p class="t-label mb-6">Work with me</p>
        <h1 class="t-display mb-6">You have the research.<br />I'll find the argument.</h1>
        <p class="t-body text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Narrative strategy for organisations sitting on strong insight that isn't working as hard as it should.
        </p>
      </header>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <section class="mb-16">
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>Most organisations that commission research publish it and move on. A report goes out, gets three articles written from it, and then sits on a server while the next brief lands.</p>
          <p>The problem isn't the research. It's that no one built the narrative layer — the argument that connects the data points, gives the findings direction, and makes the insight reusable across teams, channels and time.</p>
          <p>That's the gap I work in.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">Who this is for</h2>
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>B2B companies — typically in fintech, professional services or SaaS — where:</p>
          <ul class="work-list">
            <li>You've commissioned research that underperformed relative to what you spent on it</li>
            <li>You have years of customer insight that hasn't been turned into a coherent strategic narrative</li>
            <li>Your content programme resets with every campaign rather than compounding over time</li>
            <li>You're about to invest in more content but sense that more isn't the answer</li>
          </ul>
          <p>The right engagement starts with a clear-eyed look at what you already have.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">How it works</h2>

        <div class="engagement-block">
          <div class="engagement-header">
            <span class="engagement-number">01</span>
            <h3 class="engagement-title">Narrative audit</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="prose-section">
            <p>A structured review of your existing research, content and customer insight. I read what you have, identify what the evidence is actually saying, and assess what narrative case it supports — and what's being missed.</p>
            <p>You get a clear written assessment: what your strongest through-lines are, where the gaps are, and what a connected narrative system would look like built from your existing inputs.</p>
            <p class="engagement-outcome">Outcome: a narrative audit report. Fixed scope, fixed fee. Typically two to three weeks.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="engagement-block">
          <div class="engagement-header">
            <span class="engagement-number">02</span>
            <h3 class="engagement-title">Narrative development</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="prose-section">
            <p>From the audit, the next stage is building the narrative itself — the strategic argument, the through-lines, the framework that organises your insight into something that compounds rather than resets.</p>
            <p>This might be a narrative brief your content team works from, a framework document that makes the insight reusable, or a content system structure that connects your existing and future assets.</p>
            <p class="engagement-outcome">Outcome: defined with you based on what the audit surfaces.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="engagement-block">
          <div class="engagement-header">
            <span class="engagement-number">03</span>
            <h3 class="engagement-title">Ongoing advisory</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="prose-section">
            <p>For teams that want a strategic editorial perspective on an ongoing basis — reviewing how new research connects to existing narratives, sense-checking content decisions against the strategic argument, and identifying when the narrative needs to evolve.</p>
            <p class="engagement-outcome">Outcome: retainer-based. Scope defined per engagement.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">What I bring</h2>
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>A decade of content and editorial work, mostly in B2B — building research programmes, developing strategic narratives, and connecting organisational knowledge into systems that outlast individual campaigns.</p>
          <p>The work on this site documents that practice: <a href="/narratives/hidden-hours" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">Hidden Hours</a> is a research programme that became a multi-year editorial platform. <a href="/narratives/winning-in-small" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">Winning in Small</a> is a narrative that emerged from synthesising events, customer insight and survey data into a coherent strategic argument. The <a href="/practice" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">In Practice</a> page shows how these things connect.</p>
          <p>I'm not an agency. I work on a small number of engagements at a time, which means the thinking is mine rather than delegated.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">Get in touch</h2>
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>If you're working on this kind of problem — or not sure yet whether you are — the best first step is a conversation.</p>
          <p>
            <a href="mailto:asavin@contentconsultant.net" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">asavin@contentconsultant.net</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .work-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .work-list li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .work-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .engagement-block {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule, #2c2920);
  }

  .engagement-block:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .engagement-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .engagement-number {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .engagement-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .engagement-outcome {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem !important;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary) !important;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
